Topic1: Variables
-----------------

syntax:
	variable_name="value"
	
	Rules:
	.No space around=
	.Quotes required only when values contain spaces
	.Variable reference uses $var or "${var}"
	
	Example:
	#!/bin/bash
	name="linux"
	echo "Welcome to $name learning"
	
Environment Varibles:
---------------------
Environment variables are global and inherited processes.

common variables
----------------
variable			Meaning
---------------------------
$USER				Logged-in user
$HOME				Home directory path
$PATH				Path where executables are searched
$PWD				Current working directory	


#!/bin/bash
name=shiva
echo "my name is $name"


#Example2: Number variable
count=20
echo "Count is $count"


# Example3: Print system variables
echo "User: $USER"
echo "Home directory: $HOME"
echo "Current directory: $PWD"
echo "Shell: $SHELL"

#Example4: Store a command output
date_now=$(date)
echo "Current date is: $date_now"
